text: The 2016 United States presidential election in Arizona was held on 8 November 2016. It was part of the 2016 United States presidential election, in which all other states plus the District of Columbia voted. On 22 March and 5 April 2016, the state also voted for who they wanted to be the nominee of their respective parties. == Presidential == === Polling === Below is a table with the polling results in Arizona. Arizona has voted Republican in the general election since 2000.
